Hi @pierresh!

You can create your own custom filter row ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/729pgngw/)), or add the name attribute within a callback bound to the [`filterInit` event](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#filterinit):

Custom HTML Row:

```html
<tr class="tablesorter-ignoreRow filters">
  <td><input name="foo" type="search" data-column="0" /></td>
  <td><input name="bar" type="search" data-column="1" /></td>
  ...
</tr>
```

Script

```js
$(function() {
  $('table').tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    widgets: ['zebra', 'filter'],
    widgetOptions: {
      filter_columnFilters: false,
      filter_external: 'tr.filters input'
    }
  });
});
```

