I added the @api.expect() decorator as a shortcut for @api.doc(body=).
Both supports specifying a type wrapped in an array.

In your case, you can write:
```python
@api.route('/somewhere')
class MyAPI(Resource):
    @api.expect([mymodel])
    def post(self):
        pass
```
or
In your case, you can write:
```python
@api.route('/somewhere')
class MyAPI(Resource):
    @api.doc(body=[mymodel])
    def post(self):
        pass
```

