@clintinthecode accurate estimation of sync time is a very complex matter due to high transfer start/stop time and two highly probable network bottlenecks (on both upload and download). A disk bottleneck can also be an important factor, as it was shown in another issue (where someone has set the amount of reading threads to 200).

Accurate sync estimation was not a high priority for b2 CLI team, at least until now. Misleading estimate could be worse than nothing.

We already have some support for customizable progress reporting functionality - if you'd like to work on this, then we could help you connect your advanced estimator with the b2 CLI library. This way you could implement the progress reporting without worrying about all the stuff the CLI already does (exponential back-off after server-side failure, retrying in case of transient errors, authorization, handling tokens etc). This would benefit all parties, providing a nice interface and high quality estimation... that is, if you want to take a shot at implementing something like this. Will you?

