Just realised I can override the configured values with [Git environment variables](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Environment-Variables). The following ensures the commit author is the author of the incoming build:

```
export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=$(git --no-pager show -s --format='%an' HEAD)
export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=$(git --no-pager show -s --format='%ae' HEAD)
```

(the git committer remains "doctr", which is perfect)

Had been struggling with the same issue after adopting crispy forms and found an insanely easy fix:

<form method="post" action="" class="">
           {% crispy form %}
           
           {{ formset.management_form|crispy }}
           {% for form in formset %}
                <div class="form-inline">
                         {% crispy form %}
                </div>
</form>

That's it.  I set the helper attributes and layout at the form level.  Did get rid of self.helper.form_class in the attributes.  Did not set any individual field attributes to inline.  Setting the div class around the form did the trick.

