The error in the test comes from the fact that `manager-base` expects the model to define attributes like `_view_name` in the state, but the test model doesn't provide those. They then get serialised to `null`, which causes the code in `WidgetModel$serialize` to fail because `null` doesn't have a `toJSON` property.

AFAICT, there are two ways to make the test pass.

1. Allow models to not pass in required properties like `_view_name` by changing this:

```javascript
                if (state[k].toJSON) {
                    state[k] = state[k].toJSON();
                }
```

to this:

```
                if (state[k] && state[k].toJSON) {
                    state[k] = state[k].toJSON();
                }
```

I'm not sure what the implications of having an incomplete model are.

2. Give the test-widget a non-null value for `_view_name`.

Some guidance here would be great.
